A 53-year-old suspect is set to appear before the Madadeni Magistrate’s Court this morning, 18 June for allegedly raping a schoolgirl. “It is alleged that on 9 June, an eleven-year-old girl was at a school in Madadeni when she was raped by one of the teachers in the school toilets. She was threatened to be killed should she report the matter to anyone,” said Captain Nqobile Gwala. The victim informed her mother about the incident and a case of rape was opened at Madadeni SAPS. The docket was transferred to Newcastle Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit for further investigation.  The suspect was arrested yesterday morning by the FCS Unit. This is a developing story and updates will follow when new information is available.